.SH NAME
HTMLSelectElement.size \- HTMLSelectElement: size property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]size\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLSelectElement\f[R] interface specifies the number of options,
or rows, that should be visible at one time.
It reflects the \f[CR]<select>\f[R] element\[cq]s \f[CR]size\f[R]
attribute.
If omitted, the value is \f[CR]0\f[R].
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] While by default a \f[CR]<select>\f[R] displays a single
row unless \f[CR]multiple\f[R] is true, in which case four rows are
displayed, the default value for the \f[CR]size\f[R] property is
\f[CR]0\f[R].
.RE
.SH VALUE
A number.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] selectElement = document.getElementById(\[dq]fruits\[dq]);
console.log(selectElement.size);
.EE
